"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674225","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-24","<p>The number of non-commissioned personnel that have received International Defence Training in the UK over the last five financial years (FY) is shown below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>FY</p></td><td><p>Numbers of Non Commissioned Personnel Trained in the UK</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>678</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>595</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>664</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>754</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>619</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figure for FY2016-17 is a projection for the whole year.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","60364","2017-01-24T15:07:09.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674225/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674225/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) officers and (b) officer cadets from overseas militaries have received training in the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674226","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-24","<p>The number of non-commissioned personnel that have received International Defence Training in the UK over the last five financial years (FY) is shown below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>FY</p></td><td><p>Numbers of Non Commissioned Personnel Trained in the UK</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>678</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>595</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>664</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>754</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>619</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figure for FY2016-17 is a projection for the whole year.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","60363","2017-01-24T15:07:09.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674226/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674226/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many non-commissioned personnel from overseas militaries have received training in the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674227","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-23","<p>The King’s Royal Hussars are planned to be the first Field Army unit to receive AJAX in 2019.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-23T17:50:03.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674227/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674227/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which of the army's regiments he plans will receive the first Ajax armoured fighting vehicle.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674228","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-24","<p>On 8 July 2016, the former Prime Minister announced that the previous exclusions on women serving in Ground Close Combat roles in the Royal Marines, Royal Armoured Corps (RAC), Infantry and Royal Air Force Regiment were being lifted. The implementation is in a phased approach over the next three years, beginning with the RAC which is open now with other roles opening from 2018.</p><p>As at 20 January 2017, there are no female Regular or Reserve officers and less than five female Regular and Reserve soldiers serving in Ground Close Combat units.</p><p>Marketing and recruiting material now ensures that women are aware that the RAC is open to them, and applications to join or transfer to the RAC are being processed.</p><p>Please note that all figures have been rounded to the nearest five as a means of disclosure control to preserve anonymity.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","60379","2017-01-24T15:05:24.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674228/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674228/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Army: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many female (a) officers and (b) non-commissioned personnel are currently serving in ground close combat units.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674229","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-24","<p>On 8 July 2016, the former Prime Minister announced that the previous exclusions on women serving in Ground Close Combat roles in the Royal Marines, Royal Armoured Corps (RAC), Infantry and Royal Air Force Regiment were being lifted. The implementation is in a phased approach over the next three years, beginning with the RAC which is open now with other roles opening from 2018.</p><p>As at 20 January 2017, there are no female Regular or Reserve officers and less than five female Regular and Reserve soldiers serving in Ground Close Combat units.</p><p>Marketing and recruiting material now ensures that women are aware that the RAC is open to them, and applications to join or transfer to the RAC are being processed.</p><p>Please note that all figures have been rounded to the nearest five as a means of disclosure control to preserve anonymity.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","60378","2017-01-24T15:05:24.353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674229/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674229/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Army: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to raise public awareness of opportunities available to women in ground close combat roles.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60379"
