"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674391","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-20","<p>In November and December 2016 the Green Investment Bank (GIB) incorporated twelve new Special Purpose Vehicles (SPVs): Galloper Holdco Limited; OSW Co Holdings 1 Limited; OSW Co Holdings 2 Limited; OSW LP Holdco Limited; Project G Holdco Limited; Project G Holdings 1 Limited; Project G Holdings 2 Limited; Rampion Holdco Limited; WMR Holdco Limited; Rampion Investco Limited; New Green Interim Holdco Limited; and UK Green Investment Lyle Limited.</p><p>The SPV ‘UK Green Investment Lyle Limited’ was incorporated in the course of business-as-usual to support GIB’s investment in the Lincs offshore wind farm (publicly announced by GIB on 13 January 2017).</p><p>The remaining eleven SPVs were incorporated in order to facilitate the potential introduction of private capital in to a number of GIB’s offshore wind assets, following discussion between GIB and the UK Government. These entities are currently dormant and own no assets.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","60233 ; 60234 ; 60235 ; 60236","2017-01-20T14:48:26.18Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674391/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674391/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 13 January 2017 to Question 59325, whether private capital had been secured for the offshore wind assets before the decision to establish the new companies was taken.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","60232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674392","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-20","<p>In November and December 2016 the Green Investment Bank (GIB) incorporated twelve new Special Purpose Vehicles (SPVs): Galloper Holdco Limited; OSW Co Holdings 1 Limited; OSW Co Holdings 2 Limited; OSW LP Holdco Limited; Project G Holdco Limited; Project G Holdings 1 Limited; Project G Holdings 2 Limited; Rampion Holdco Limited; WMR Holdco Limited; Rampion Investco Limited; New Green Interim Holdco Limited; and UK Green Investment Lyle Limited.</p><p>The SPV ‘UK Green Investment Lyle Limited’ was incorporated in the course of business-as-usual to support GIB’s investment in the Lincs offshore wind farm (publicly announced by GIB on 13 January 2017).</p><p>The remaining eleven SPVs were incorporated in order to facilitate the potential introduction of private capital in to a number of GIB’s offshore wind assets, following discussion between GIB and the UK Government. These entities are currently dormant and own no assets.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","60232 ; 60234 ; 60235 ; 60236","2017-01-20T14:48:26.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674392/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674392/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 13 January 2017 to Question 59325, whether nominated trustees of the special share company of the Green Investment Bank were alerted to the establishment of new companies.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","60233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674393","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-20","<p>In November and December 2016 the Green Investment Bank (GIB) incorporated twelve new Special Purpose Vehicles (SPVs): Galloper Holdco Limited; OSW Co Holdings 1 Limited; OSW Co Holdings 2 Limited; OSW LP Holdco Limited; Project G Holdco Limited; Project G Holdings 1 Limited; Project G Holdings 2 Limited; Rampion Holdco Limited; WMR Holdco Limited; Rampion Investco Limited; New Green Interim Holdco Limited; and UK Green Investment Lyle Limited.</p><p>The SPV ‘UK Green Investment Lyle Limited’ was incorporated in the course of business-as-usual to support GIB’s investment in the Lincs offshore wind farm (publicly announced by GIB on 13 January 2017).</p><p>The remaining eleven SPVs were incorporated in order to facilitate the potential introduction of private capital in to a number of GIB’s offshore wind assets, following discussion between GIB and the UK Government. These entities are currently dormant and own no assets.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","60232 ; 60233 ; 60235 ; 60236","2017-01-20T14:48:26.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674393/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674393/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 13 January 2017 to Question 59325, whether Ministers or officials of his Department were aware at the time of the creation of 10 new subsidiary companies at the Green Investment Bank in November and December 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","60234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674394","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-23","<p>Information on individual staff roles and the percentage of time spent on specific tasks is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-01-23T14:04:15.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674394/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674394/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the number of employees in his Department working in full-time business support roles in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","60287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674395","Cabinet Office","false","2017-01-25","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-01-25T16:41:43.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674395/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674395/answer","PQ60288 v.02.pdf","PQ60288 v.02.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Small Business Closure","UKSA Letter to Member - Small Business Closure","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674395/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-01-17","Small Businesses: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of small businesses that have closed in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","60288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674396","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-25","<p>This Government wants the UK to be the go-to place for innovators and investors across the world, and we intend to secure the right outcome for the UK research base as we exit the European Union.</p><p>As my rt hon. Friend the Prime Minister has said, we would welcome an agreement to continue to collaborate with our European partners on major science, research, and technology initiatives. However it is too early to speculate on the UK’s future relationship with specific EU research programmes, including Horizon 2020 and successor programmes.</p><p>The Government is committed to ensuring the UK remains a world leader in international research and innovation.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-01-25T13:58:53.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674396/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674396/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Horizon 2020","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will prioritise maintaining access to Horizon 2020 funding for UK researchers during negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","60308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674397","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Government has set out its plans for the sale of the Green Investment Bank (GIB) in the document “Green Investment Bank: sale of shares” laid before Parliament on 3 March 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The special share will be held by an independent company – the Green Purposes Company Limited, with trustees who have been selected independently of Government and of GIB. The independent trustees will have the right to approve or reject any proposed change to the green purposes of GIB, as set out in the company’s Articles of Association, if such a change were ever proposed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","60281","2017-01-24T14:09:03.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674397/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674397/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the role is of the trustees of the special share company of the Green Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","60280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674398","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Government has set out its plans for the sale of the Green Investment Bank (GIB) in the document “Green Investment Bank: sale of shares” laid before Parliament on 3 March 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The special share will be held by an independent company – the Green Purposes Company Limited, with trustees who have been selected independently of Government and of GIB. The independent trustees will have the right to approve or reject any proposed change to the green purposes of GIB, as set out in the company’s Articles of Association, if such a change were ever proposed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","60280","2017-01-24T14:09:03.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674398/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674398/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the trustees of the special share company of the Green Investment Bank will authorise individual investment proposals.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","60281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674399","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-01-24","<p>The sale process is currently ongoing and neither Government nor the Green Investment Bank are able to provide any update on the identity of any bidders.</p><p> </p><p>All parties have been required to sign confidentiality agreements and these place strict restrictions on the disclosure of information. These restrictions apply both to bidders and the Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-01-24T14:10:17.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674399/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674399/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-01-17","Green Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many staff at the Green Investment Bank have previously worked for the Government's preferred bidder for the Government's shares in that bank.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","60282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674400","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-20","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) are actively building bilateral trade links between the UK and Iraq, supported by the work of the Iraq Britain Business Council and the PM Trade Envoy to Iraq Baroness Nicholson.</p><p>The Ambassador regularly raises trade issues with Prime Minister Abadi and in the last six weeks, along with DIT colleagues, has met with the President of Iraq and the Ministers of Electricity, Construction, Oil and Transport to support commercial opportunities for British companies. As a result, DIT has helped British companies win significant contracts in the air services, security and infrastructure sectors, with British companies competing for more business.</p><p>The full range of medium and long-term UK Export Finance (UKEF) facilities is available to support UK exports to Iraq. UKEF has received expressions of interest from a number of businesses across a range of sectors. In December, UKEF supported UK exporter Biwater to deliver water treatment solutions in the Kurdistan Region of Iraq.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-01-20T14:48:05.287Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674400/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674400/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-17","Overseas Trade: Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what recent steps his Department has taken to promote bilateral trade between the UK and Iraq; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","60312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674401","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-25","<p>Central America and Mexico are currently part of the following high value trade campaigns: Automotive, Defence, Technology, Airports, Education, Financial Services, Food &amp; Drink, Healthcare, Mining, Oil &amp; Gas, Railways and Water. The Department for International Trade (DIT) resource delivering these campaigns includes staff time and business development activity. The level of resource varies according to the scale of the opportunity for UK companies to export to each market.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-01-25T15:25:33.113Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674401/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674401/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-17","Trade Promotion: Central America","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 47641, on Trade promotion: Central America, what campaigns have received resources to access high-value sectors in Central America; and what resources each of those campaigns has received.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","60291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674402","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-25","<p>Central America sits within the Department for International Trade's (DIT) Latin America regional directorate. DIT currently has staff in 12 countries in the region. Following the machinery of government changes after the appointment of the Prime Minister in July 2016, updated details of Trade Offices will be published in due course. In the meantime, details can be found within the Exporting country guides on Gov.uk.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-01-25T13:50:19.903Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674402/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674402/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-17","Trade Promotion: Central America","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, where in Central America has a permanent UK trade office.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","60250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674403","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-25","<p>The reciprocal entitlements that will apply following the UK’s exit are subject to the wider negotiation on our future relationship with the EU. We will approach negotiations with the full intention of securing a deal that delivers the best possible outcome for the UK and its nationals wherever they are living. It goes without saying that we want a smooth and orderly exit from the EU, and will look at the best way to deliver that.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2017-01-25T16:10:02.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674403/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674403/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","State Retirement Pensions: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment he has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on state pensions paid to UK nationals living in EEA countries.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674404","Department for International Trade","false","2017-01-25","<p>I refer the hon Member for North East Fife to the answer I gave him on 23 January 2017, UIN: 59936.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-01-25T13:48:59.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674404/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674404/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-01-17","Developing Countries: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU on exporters from developing countries.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","60204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674405","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-23","<p>All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK. The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 300 staff, and is growing fast. As the Department is currently recruiting a large number of staff we do not currently hold a full data set, but diversity data will be published in due course in line with CS reporting requirements.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-23T14:50:20.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674405/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674405/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","Department for Exiting the European Union: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many staff his Department has recruited since June 2016; what proportion of those staff identify as (a) female, (b) male and (c) another gender; what proportion of the total number of staff recruited identify as BAME; and what proportion of that total number has negotiation expertise.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","60283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674406","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that the current Customs Union arrangement with the EU would prevent us from negotiating our own comprehensive free trade agreements. But she was also clear that we want a customs agreement with the EU. ​</p><p>No final decisions about the UK's future customs arrangements with the EU has yet been taken. There are a number of aspects to this and our aim is to get the best possible deal in the negotiation. However, even where we currently apply customs requirements on trade with the rest of the world, it is not the case that every shipping container needs to be inspected at its port of entry into the UK.</p><p><strong><br></strong></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T14:32:49.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674406/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674406/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","Shipping: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether UK withdrawal from the EU customs union would result in a requirement for every shipping container to be inspected at its port of entry into the UK.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674407","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>We want to have reached an agreement about our future partnership, which will cover issues such as fisheries, by the time the two-year Article 50 process has concluded.</p><p>We seek a new and equal partnership – between an independent, self-governing, Global Britain and our friends and allies in the EU. As we negotiate that partnership, we will be driven by some simple principles: we will provide as much certainty and clarity as we can at every stage.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T11:57:08.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674407/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674407/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he plans for negotiations on fisheries to be conducted separately or within general Article 50 negotiations.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","60267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674408","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>As the Prime Minister set out in her speech, one of the objectives for the negotiations ahead is to continue practical cooperation with the EU to tackle cross-border crime and to keep our people safe.</p><p><strong><br></strong>As part of the negotiations, we will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue cooperation on security, law enforcement and criminal justice.<strong><br></strong></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T11:35:40.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674408/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674408/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","Eurojust and Europol: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the Government's policy is on membership of (a) Europol, (b) Eurojust and (c) the European Arrest Warrant Scheme after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674409","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>As part of the exit negotiations the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue cooperation in the field of aviation safety and standards. It would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T11:25:59.397Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674409/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674409/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","European Aviation Safety Agency: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the Government's policy is on membership of the European Aviation Safety Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674410","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>As part of the exit negotiations the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue cooperation in the field of medicines regulation in the best interests of both the UK and the EU. It would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T11:31:49.923Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674410/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674410/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","European Medicines Agency: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the Government's policy is on membership of the European Medicines Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674411","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>As the Prime Minister outlined in her speech on Monday 17 January, we will pursue a bold and ambitious Free Trade Agreement with the European Union that should allow for the freest possible trade in goods and services between Britain and the EU’s member states. It should give British companies the maximum freedom to trade with and operate within European markets – and let European businesses do the same in Britain.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T13:11:38.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674411/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674411/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 20 December 2016 to Question 57205, whether the policy of the Government remains giving UK companies the maximum freedom to trade with and operate in the Single Market while letting European businesses do the same in the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","60381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674412","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-20","<p>We want Britain to have the greatest possible tariff and barrier-free trade in goods and services with our European neighbours and also to be able to negotiate our own trade agreements.</p><p>The Department for Exiting the European Union, working with officials across government, continues to undertake a wide range of data analysis covering the entirety of the UK economy. We are looking at over 50 sectors as well as cross-cutting regulatory issues. This will inform the UK's position for the upcoming negotiations with our EU partners.</p><p>As the Prime Minister has said, the government's plan for leaving the EU will be discussed at length. But as Parliament has also agreed, we will not publish anything that would undermine our ability to negotiate the best deal for Britain.</p><p><strong><br></strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-20T12:53:31.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674412/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674412/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will publish his economic assessments of the different options for market access and trade to accompany the Government's plan for leaving the EU as set out by the Prime Minister in her speech at Lancaster House on 17 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","60422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674425","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-24","<p>The apprenticeship levy takes effect from April 2017. The expected yield for the apprenticeship levy for each financial year from 2017-18 to 2021-22 is published in table C.5: ‘Current Receipts’, in the Autumn Statement 2016 document available here: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/571559/autumn_statement_2016_web.pdf</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-01-24T10:22:01.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674425/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674425/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate how much his Department expects to accrue to the public purse in this financial year from the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","60465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674426","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-25","<p>On 8 November, the Chancellor of the Exchequer and Home Secretary updated the House on the progress of the cross-agency taskforce that was set up to analyse and take action on the International Consortium of Investigative Journalists’ Panama Papers data leak (HCWS247).</p><p> </p><p>As part of this update, they confirmed that HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) had opened civil and criminal investigations into 22 individuals for suspected tax evasion, and has placed 43 high net worth individuals under special review while their links to Panama are further investigated.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC will engage the relevant prosecuting authorities to bring any identified wrongdoing before the courts. On 7 December, it confirmed that two arrests had been made as part of a criminal investigation involving the use of a number of offshore companies to disguise the beneficial ownership of UK property.</p><p> </p><p>As stated previously, Parliament will be kept updated on any significant developments.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-01-25T15:24:15.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674426/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674426/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the cross-agency task force investigating the so-called Panama Papers will make its first progress report to Parliament.","false","Biography information for Dr Rupa Huq","Ealing Central and Acton","Dr Rupa Huq","60460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674427","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-25","<p>The UK launched an initiative with the EU G5 for the systematic exchange of beneficial ownership information in April 2016. More than 50 jurisdictions, including all Crown Dependencies and Overseas Territories with a significant financial sector, have now signed up. Work is ongoing on the development of the initiative.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-01-25T15:22:26.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674427/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674427/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Companies: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the private registers of beneficial ownership currently being created by the UK's Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies will be incorporated into the UK's existing exchange of information pertaining to beneficial ownership with France, Spain, Germany and Italy.","false","Biography information for Dr Rupa Huq","Ealing Central and Acton","Dr Rupa Huq","60459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674428","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-25","<p>The taper of the Personal Allowance for those earning above £100,000 is estimated to have accrued £2.7 billion in income tax in 2015-16, £2.4 billion in 2014-15 and £2.2 billion in 2013-14. Changes to the tax system affecting high income individuals involve significant behavioural responses which can impact revenues from such measures.</p><p>The Personal Allowance taper was introduced by the last Labour government. While the Government recognises that this feature of the income tax system can cause high marginal tax rates, the continued pressure on the public finances mean that the Government has been unable to remove it to date.</p><p>The estimates in this response are based on the 2013-14 Survey of Personal Incomes, projected to 2015-16 using economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s November 2016 Economic and Fiscal Outlook.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-01-25T15:30:55.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674428/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674428/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much has accrued to the public purse through the removal of personal allowances for annual incomes in excess of £100,000 in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Conor Burns","Bournemouth West","Conor Burns","60464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674429","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-20","<p>The Treasury’s role is to set an annual budget allocation for renewable heat schemes in Northern Ireland proportionate to the budget provided to the department which manages similar schemes in Great Britain. Administering the scheme, including the disbursal of payments to recipients, is the responsibility of the relevant Northern Ireland Executive departments.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2017-01-20T10:10:52.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674429/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674429/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Northern Ireland Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether AME funding for the Northern Ireland non-domestic renewable heat incentive continued on an interrupted basis from 1 April 2015 to 30 September 2015.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","60493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674430","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-20","<p>All spending on the Northern Ireland Renewable Heat Incentive is ‘devolved spending’ in respect of the Northern Ireland Executive’s devolved responsibilities.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2017-01-20T10:09:14.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674430/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674430/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Northern Ireland Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether any misuse of funds attached to the uptake of the Northern Ireland non-domestic renewable heating incentive was confined to devolved spending only and did not entail use of AME funds.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","60474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674431","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-20","<p>Neither the Treasury, nor the NAO, would expect to be notified of interactions between departments of the Northern Ireland Executive in relation to internal Northern Ireland Executive spending approval processes.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2017-01-20T10:06:35.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674431/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674431/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-17","Northern Ireland Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether (a) his Department and (b) the National Audit Office were notified that the Northern Ireland Department for Finance and Personnel had declined to give retrospective approval for spending on the non-domestic renewable heat incentive scheme from 1 April 2015 to 30 September 2015.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","60494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674433","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-20","<p>Initial figures for homes built on land released by the Homes and Communities Agency during the 2011-15 Public Land for Housing programme will be included in the Annual Report for the 2015-20 Public Land for Housing programme, due to be published shortly.</p><p>Details on the number of home completions on land sold by all government departments and their agencies in both the 2011-15 and 2015-20 Public Land for Housing programmes will be published on an annual basis from summer 2017 in subsequent annual reports.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-01-20T14:18:49.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674433/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674433/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-17","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many homes have been built on spare public land sold by the Government in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","60498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674434","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-20","<p>There are no implications for the F-35 Lightning II programme. All the issues that have been raised in the annual report are known and are under active management by the Joint Strike Fighter Joint Programme Office, and the UK Ministry of Defence.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-20T13:46:56.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674434/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674434/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the implications for his Department's policies are of the US Department of Defense Director, Operational Test and Evaluation 2016 Annual Report on the F35 Joint Strike Fighter; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","60499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674435","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-25","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) undertakes substantial purchases of fuel commodities. Exposure to fluctuations in the market prices of these commodities is hedged to obtain budget certainty on price rather than seek speculative gains.</p><p> </p><p>The Department hedges up to three years in advance and usually trades quarterly to further spread price risk. This approach has been used for fuel hedging since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the volume of fuel procured by the Department is not centrally held but in Financial Year 2015-16 the MOD procured approximately £356 million of fuel and consumed £333 million of fuel.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","60490 ; 60491","2017-01-25T15:06:17.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674435/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674435/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-17","Fuels: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much of the fuel procured by his Department in 2015-16 was financially hedged.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60492"
