"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674499","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-25","<p>All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK. We are not in a position to give a final total for particular groups of staff as recruitment is ongoing and we will not be giving a running commentary. The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 300 staff, and is growing fast.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-01-25T15:05:51.123Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674499/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/674499/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-01-17","Department for Exiting the European Union: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many negotiators his Department has recruited to date.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675992","Home Office","false","2017-01-23","<p>The UK has an immigration system that works in the national interest, and takes account of the interests of all parts of the UK economy, including the rural economy.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-23T16:33:40.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675992/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675992/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-17","Immigration: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she has taken to ensure that immigration policy supports the rural economy.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","908299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677055","Home Office","false","2017-01-23","<p>In 2016, we transferred over 900 unaccompanied asylum-seeking children to the UK from Europe. More children will be transferred under the Immigration Act and we will continue to meet our obligations under the Dublin Regulation.</p><p>Outside of Europe, approximately half of the 4,400 Syrians resettled under the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement scheme are children, and we will resettle up to 3,000 vulnerable children and their families to the UK by the end of this Parliament.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-23T16:37:31.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677055/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677055/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-17","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what progress her Department has made on bringing vulnerable refugee children to the UK.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","908297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677056","Home Office","false","2017-01-23","<p>There were 62,518 hate crimes recorded by the police in 2015/16, an increase of 19% over the previous year. There were increases in all five hate crime strands - race, religion, sexual orientation, disability and gender identity.</p><p>Improvements in recording by the police, a greater awareness of hate crime and improved willingness of victims to come forward are likely to have led to the increase in recorded crime.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-23T16:35:55.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677056/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677056/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-17","Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of trends in the level of hate crime reporting.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","908295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677057","Home Office","false","2017-01-23","<p>Immigration remains a reserved matter and we will consider the needs of the UK as a whole.</p><p>Applying different immigration rules to different parts of the UK would complicate the immigration system, harming its integrity, and cause difficulties for employers who need the flexibility to deploy their staff to other parts of the UK.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-23T16:40:53.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677057/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677057/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677057/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-17","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make an assessment of the potential merits of applying different immigration rules to Scotland and other constituent parts of the UK.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","908302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677058","Home Office","false","2017-01-23","<p>The Government - in partnership with the fire sector - is delivering a radical and ambitious programme of reform to make the fire and rescue service more accountable, efficient and professional than ever before. This includes: creating a new independent inspectorate; enabling police and crime commissioners to take on local fire governance; supporting commercial transformation; driving transparency; forming a professional standards body and reforming the workforce to make it more flexible, skilled and diverse.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-23T16:37:51.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677058/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/677058/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-17","Fire and Rescue Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to reform the fire service.","false","Biography information for James Cleverly","Braintree","James Cleverly","908300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678285","Wales Office","false","2017-01-25","<p>The Welsh economy approaches its departure from the EU in a very strong position. Since 2010, Wales has been the fastest growing part of the UK outside London and exports to countries outside the EU have increased by £400 million.</p><p>Last week my Rt hon Friend the Prime Minister set out this Government’s plan to build a stronger, fairer, more global Britain. I am confident that Wales will grasp the opportunities presented and play its role as part of a stronger United Kingdom.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-01-25T15:16:59.643Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678285/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678285/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-01-17","Economic Situation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what recent assessment he has made of the potential effect on the Welsh economy of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","908313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678286","Wales Office","false","2017-01-25","<p>I recognise that the steel industry is still dealing with very challenging global economic conditions. I am in regular contact with the Secretary of State for Business Energy and Industrial Strategy, the steel unions and continue my dialogue with the Welsh government and local authorities. The Government has left no stone unturned supporting the steel sector. We will continue to engage with the sector, as well as with the industry stakeholders, as we seek to find a long-term viable solution for the industry.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-01-25T15:17:54.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678286/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678286/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-01-17","Iron and Steel: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what recent assessment he has made of the performance of the steel industry in Wales.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","908316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678287","Wales Office","false","2017-01-25","<p>The UK’s electricity supply remains the most reliable in Europe. Wales plays an important role in contributing to our diverse energy generation mix.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-01-25T15:15:34.23Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678287/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/678287/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-01-17","Electricity: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what assessment he has made of the security of electricity supply in Wales.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","908311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673444","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-01-23","<p>The Contract to deliver the Credit Union Expansion Project was scheduled to end in December 2016. The Association of British Credit Unions Ltd (ABCUL) are delivering the Contract and has provided a proposal to extend the delivery timeline. To allow the proposal to be considered the Department has agreed an interim Contract extension to February 2017.</p><p> </p><p>To the end of December 2016, £30.8.m has been spent. Any remaining expenditure is subject to agreement on ABCUL’s proposal to extend the Contract and delivery of specific outcomes.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-01-23T14:54:45.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673444/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673444/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-01-16","Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 12 January 2017 to Question 58730, on credit unions, what steps he plans to take to complete the expansion project for credit unions; how the £38 million will be allocated; and over what time period that allocation will take place.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Sir David Crausby","59997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673445","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-19","<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Office" target="_blank">The Office</a> for Budget Responsibility’s Economic and Fiscal Outlook (November 2016) includes the latest forecasts for oil and gas. The November Outlook indicates a downward trend in planned capital expenditure in the oil and gas sector, from £10.1 billion in 2016 to £3.7 billion in 2021. This reflects a lower oil price and its consequential effect on overall production.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has taken unprecedented action to support jobs, investment and activity in the UK and UK Continental Shelf. Budget 2016 announced a £1 billion package of fiscal reform, supporting the industry through the challenging commercial conditions caused by the steep fall in oil prices. Lower tax rates will improve the economics of new investment and future discoveries. The basin-wide Investment Allowance, introduced in 2015, further reduces the effective rate of tax for many companies, including at the exploration stage.</p><p> </p><p>As a result of these changes, the UK now has one of the most competitive tax regimes for oil and gas in the world, supporting jobs and investment.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","60018 ; 60019 ; 60020","2017-01-19T15:26:23.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673445/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/673445/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-16","Fossil Fuels: Capital Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of fiscal changes made in the Budget 2016 on capital investment in the oil and gas sector.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","60017"
